metadata.title: Rhinoceros Auklet of the Teuri Island, Hokkaido, Japan
metadata.description:
Data parameters include time of hatching, hatching success, number of fledgling per net, chick growth rate, fledgling mass, fledgling period, fledgling size, adult size and mass, prey composition, and prey fish size.   

[ Reference: PICES Scientific Report No. 18 2001, Proceedings of the PICES/CoML/IPRC Workshop on "Impact of Climate Variability on Observation and Prediction of Ecosystem and Biodiversity Changes in the North Pacific", http://www.pices.int/publications/scientific_reports/Report18/default.aspx. ]
metadata.notes:
Purpose: To analyze how annual variation of physical marine processes in the northern part of the Japan Sea affect seabird breeding performance through fish stock change.
